version: 1
display_name: VCFA-9X-000054 - VMware Cloud Foundation must use multifactor authentication for access to privileged accounts.
global_description: |-
  Without the use of multifactor authentication, the ease of access to privileged functions is greatly increased.

  Multifactor authentication requires the use of two or more factors to achieve authentication.

  Factors include:
  (i) Something a user knows (e.g., password/PIN);
  (ii) Something a user has (e.g., cryptographic identification device, token); or
  (iii) Something a user is (e.g., biometric).

  A privileged account is defined as an information system account with authorizations of a privileged user.

  Network access is defined as access to an information system by a user (or a process acting on behalf of a user) communicating through a network (e.g., local area network, wide area network, or the internet).
osfinger:
  - VMware Photon OS-5
